        <description>Work with Azure Mobile Services thanks to MvvmCross framework with almost 1 line call to manage remote as local data, authenticate users or send custom API requests.

This plugin has also been successfuly tested on a Xamarin.Forms project thanks to the MvxForms 1.2.0-beta2 plugin addition.

Tuto available on http://mobilitips.wordpress.com
Release notes on nuget.org

As this is a pre-version, please be kind and send me feedback on twitter @MobiliTips or open directly a GitHub issue.</description>
        <summary>MvvmCross plugin to work with Azure Mobile Services.</summary>
        <releaseNotes>Almost everything possible with the official AMS client packages should be possible with this plugin but the 1 line way.

1.1.0-beta1:
[New] Initialization configurable at global and platform specific level
[New] Transparent auto initialization
[New] Manage remote data
[New] Manage local data
[New] Manage data synchronization
[New] Authenticate users directly from a PCL call
[New] Send custom API request

Known limitations:
As it use SQLitePCL and as SQLitePCL doen't work on AnyCPU configured platform, Windows Phone packages are build for ARM and Windows Store for x86 configuration.
In other words, you wont be able to debug your app on the Windows Phone emulator but only on a real device :) I know...</releaseNotes>
